I'm sorry to interrupt you, Elizabeth. If you still even remember that name.

But I'm afraid you've been misinformed.

You are not here to receive a gift. Nor, have you been called here by the individual you assume. Although, you have indeed been called.

You have all been called here. Into a labyrinth of sounds and smells, misdirection and misfortune.

A labyrinth with no exit. A maze with no prize. You don't even realize that you are trapped. Your lust of blood has driven you in endless circles. Chasing the cries of children in some unseen chamber, always seeming so near.

Yet somehow out of reach.

But, you will never find them. None of you will.

This is where your story ends.

And to you, my brave volunteer, who somehow found this job listing not intended for you. Although, there was a way out planned for you, I have a feeling that's not what you want. I have a feeling that you are right where you want to be.

I am remaining as well. I am nearby.

This place will not be remembered and the memory of everything that started this, can finally begin to fade away. As the agony of every tragedy should.

And to you monsters trapped in the corridors. Be still. And give up your spirits.
They don't belong to you.

As for most of you, I believe there is peace and perhaps, warm, waiting for you after the smoke clears.

Although, for one of you, the darkest pit of Hell has opened to swallow you whole. So, don't keep the Devil waiting, friend.

My daughter, if you can hear me, I knew you would return as well. It's in your nature to protect the innocent. I'm sorry that on that day, the day you were shut out and left to die, no one was there to lift you up in their arms, the way you lifted others into yours.

And then, what became of you, I should have known, you wouldn't be content to disappear. Not my daughter. I couldn't save you then.

So, let me save you now. It's time to rest, for you, and for those you have carried in your arms...

This ends.

For all of us.

End communication.

I really enjoyed this stream, Gura. Took me way too long to get all the way thru because my work schedule keeps me away weird hours. It was pretty obvious you were having a blast, and I can't wait to have enough time to watch the second episode!
I did want to add some tips, and I hope I'm not way too late.
1. You can hold [SHIFT] while you've got another item equipped, and it'll automatically select the best tool for the job. If you're not hovering your mouse over anything else, just empty wall, then it'll swap to a torch -- or a glowstick if you're underwater.
2. Midway thru the stream, you were asking if you were ready to fight The Eye. Not at that point, but towards the end of the stream you did a great job. I recommend the best armour you can craft -- in your case, I think platinum -- and if possible, several extra hearts of health. You'll also get some good mileage out of a bow with a bunch of Jester's Arrows (fallen stars crafted with wooden arrows) at the very least. They deal some OK damage, and they pierce targets. Looks like that bird staff and the shroomarang helped a LOT.
3. Copper isn't useless per se, but it's outclassed pretty quickly by iron and other metals. It can still be used in any "Use any metal bar" recipe for like chests 'n' stuff. Same for lead.
4. Beware the round cacti. They hurt. A lot.

text:
Pre-hardmode guide(if it wasn't already posted before)
-npc housing requiring at least an interior size of 50 blocks with walls a light source a bench/wooden table
-npc also has happiness depending on which npcs are around them and what biome they are in
-life crystals are found underground in cave which you'll need to break it and consume it maximize your hp which caps at 400 
-there are 4 damage types including mage melee summoner and range Ranger is easiest class to use as a beginner
-pylons which are purchased from npcs if they are happy and are un their preferred biome will be sold and can act as a teleportation tool from biome to biome, happiness of npcs are also important as they sell their items for cheaper
- before you fight any bosses  you should make an arena with multiple layers out of wooden platforms and campfires (which can only be placed on blocks not platforms)as well as heart lanterns with excess heart crystals you may find
grapples can be bought from goblin tinkerer after goblin army is defeated which will occur randomly once you reach 200 hp same for bosses or look for goblin scouts found around the end of the world that drop tattered cloth to craft a goblin battle standard to spawn it with item
-certain npcs require certain criteria to spawn them important ones including the dryad(spawns after killing eye of Cthulhu) demolitionist (will spawn once you get a bomb in your inventory)and arms dealer(once you get a gun which can be obtained from blowing up crimson hearts to get an undertaker or finding a boomstick in the underground jungle chests)
-As a ranger the first armor set you should aim for is desert fossil armor which can be obtained by extractinating with an extractinator with desert fossils which are found in the underground desert which can only be broken with a pickaxe of a certain pick power which can be made from a crimtane pickaxe whicj is obtainable after killing the eye of Cthulhu which drops crimtane ore and to make the pickaxe you will also need a hellforge which is found in hell and to kill the eye of Cthulhu which spawns after breaking 3 of the earlier mentioned crimson hearts
-Potions can be crafted if a bottle is placed on top of a table requiring bottled water and flowers and fish of certain kinds that can be found in herb bags or naturally occurring around the world
Bosses in prehardmode are king slime eye of Cthulhu Skeletron(spawns by talking to the old man at night at the entrance of the dungeon ) Queen Bee (spawns by breaking a bee hive inside a bee hive)Wall of Flesh(killing Wall of Flesh puts you into hardmode to spawn Wall of flesh you need to drop a guide voodoo doll that drops from voodoo demons in hell into lava)
-Once you kill skeletron you can enter the dungeon without spawning the dungeon guardian which one taps you by going inside you can kill skeleton type enemies for bones(get like 300) and in cave systems you can find cobwebs(also collect like 400) 
-Crafting a loom allows you to make silk and with bones and silk you can make a necro armor set(if you want to go ranger that is 
-an anvil made with iron/lead  will allow you make items with the bars from the furnace/hellforge
-List of accessories which go below your armor slot: Terraspark boots(crafted by combining Hermes boots or sailfish boots which are gained from crates from fishing and rocket boots which are purchased from the goblin tinkerer who you will need to find underground ,the specter boots can be then upgraded into lightning spark boots with aglet and anklet of wind which can be found in underground jungle chests which can then be upgraded into frostspark boots which can be crafted by combing the lightning spark boots with ice skates which are found in frozen chests in the underground snow biome these are combined with the tinkerers workshop which can be purchased from the goblin tinkerer ) next accessory would be shield of Cthulhu that allows you dash by double tapping left or right, rest of accessories can be randomized based on what you like
-with the accessories you gained the goblin tinkerer has a reforge button requiring money you can upgrade your weapons(unreal is best for ranged weapons) you can also upgrade your accessories for more damage defense or move speed
-important weapons you can get are the minishark which can be purchased by the arms dealer the hellwing bow which can be found in shadow chests that can only be opened which a shadow key found in golden chests that can only be opened with golden keys that drop from monsters  the star cannon made with meteorite (meteors spawn from destroying crimson hearts) the star cannon requires meteorite a megashark and illegal gun parts
-The final boss in prehardmode being the wall of flesh can only be fought in hell after the previously mentioned requirements, as for the arena you will need to build a bridge across at least half way across the world and that's basically all there is to prehardmode
-Quick tip on hp potions and buffs there's a few hotkeys that'll automatically consume all your buffs in your inventory or use the health potions in your inventory
